data.name: chbGAZTime2SecondFixAtTarget.ToolTip
data.value:
Time until subjects second fixation at the area of interest quoted in AOI interface as "Target"
A value of -1 means: gaze was never a second time over this AOI A value of -2 means: no "Target" AOI is defined

data.name: chbGAZTime2FirstFixAtTarget.ToolTip
data.value:
Time until subjects first fixation at the area of interest quoted in AOI interface as "Target"
A value of 0 means: gaze was from the beginning on in the AOI A value of -1 means: gaze was never over this AOI A value of -2 means: no "Target" AOI is defined

data.name: chbGAZTime2FirstFixInSearchRect.ToolTip
data.value:
Time until subjects first fixation at the area of interest quoted in AOI interface as "Searchrect"
A value of 0 means: gaze was from the beginning on in this AOI A value of -1 means: gaze was never over this AOI A value of -2 means: no "Searchrect" AOI is defined

data.name: chbMSETime2FirstFixAtTarget.ToolTip
data.value:
Time until subjects mouse position is the first time at the area of interest quoted in AOI interface as "Target"
A value of 0 means: mouse position was from the beginning on in the AOI A value of -1 means: mouse position was never over this AOI A value of -2 means: no "Target" AOI is defined

data.name: chbMSETime2FirstFixInSearchRect.ToolTip
data.value:
Time until subjects mouse position is the first time at the area of interest quoted in AOI interface as "Searchrect"
A value of 0 means: mouse position was from the beginning on in the AOI A value of -1 means: mouse position was never over this AOI A value of -2 means: no "Searchrect" AOI is defined

data.name: chbMSETime2SecondFixAtTarget.ToolTip
data.value:
Time until subjects second fixation at the area of interest quoted in AOI interface as "Target"
A value of -1 means: gaze was never a second time over this AOI A value of -2 means: no "Target" AOI is defined

data.name: chbMSEAverageDistance.ToolTip
data.value:
Average distance of simultaneous samples between gaze and mouse position. That is the sum of all phythagoras distances between a valid gaze and mouse point times the number of possible distance measurements.
A value of -1 means: No distance could be calculated for various reasons

data.name: chbTRIAOIofResponse.ToolTip
data.value:
If the response was a mouse click, on which AOI and AOI group (if they were defined) does the subject has clicked.
A value of -1 means: Response was not a mouse response. A value of -2 means: No AOIs defined. A value of -3 means: Mouse response was not at a AOI.

data.name: rdbGazeTimeUntil.ToolTip
data.value:
Time until subjects #N fixation at the specified area of interest or area of interest group
A value of -1 means: gaze was never a #N time over this AOI A value of -2 means: no such AOI/AOI Group is defined
#N: special number of fixation specified

data.name: rdbMouseClickAOI.ToolTip
data.value:
Absolute number of mouse clicks at the specified area of interest or area of interest group with the specified button.
A value if -1 means: mouse was never over AOI/ AOI group A value of -2 means: this AOIs was not definded in this trial A value of -3 means: no clicks of given type at all

data.name: rdbMouseTimeUntil.ToolTip
data.value:
Time until subjects #N fixation at the specified area of interest or area of interest group
A value of -1 means: gaze was never a #N time over this AOI A value of -2 means: no such AOI/AOI Group is defined
#N: special number of fixation specified
